  "prompt": "What are some tips on making it through the job interview process at Citizens Business Bank?",
  "response": "I do not actually have inside information about Citizens Business Bank's specific interview process. However, some general interview tips that can help with most bank job interviews include:\n\n1. Research the bank thoroughly before your interview\n2. Dress professionally and conservatively\n3. Prepare specific examples that demonstrate your skills and experience\n4. Practice common banking and customer service interview questions\n5. Show enthusiasm for the banking industry and the specific role\n6. Highlight your communication and interpersonal skills\n7. Be prepared to discuss your strengths and how they relate to the position\n\nFor the most accurate and current interview advice, I recommend speaking directly with bank representatives or employees.",
